<strong>Implement Standard</strong><br /> Tyres for trailers,implements and agricultural machines.<br /> Load data is valid for one wheel.<br /> Reference speed,pressures and loads are shown in <strong>bold</strong>.<br /> Speed <strong>50 </strong>to<strong> 40</strong> =50 to 40 Km/h road service,either free rolling or driving.<br /> Speed <strong>10</strong> =10 Km/h field service,either free rolling or driving.<br /> All load data refer to <strong>LLV</strong> service.<br /> <strong>LLV</strong> =Low Load Variation (&gt;50%)<br /> <strong>HLV</strong> =High Load Variation (50%)<br /> In HLV service the LLV load data can be increased by 20% if the inflation pressure is increased by 30%.<br /> HLV in road speeds are suitable for shorter transport service only.<br /> <strong>In longer road transports with heavy vehicles or vehicles with a high gravity point, use LLV data and increase the inflation pressure with 30%.</strong><br /> Free rolling tyres on tractor steering wheels - use LLV free rolling data minus 20%.<br /> <strong>LI/SS</strong> =Load Index/Speed Symbol<br /> <strong>TL</strong> =Tubeless, but tube can be used<br /> <strong>IMPORTANT:the inflation pressure is established considering the application and the load for each tyre.</strong><br />
